    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>DEAL FOR THAMES WATER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Suzanne Kapner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Kapner, Suzanne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>German utility company RWE AG will buy Thames Water PLC of Britain for 6.7 billion pounds and assumed debt, about $9.4 billion; Thames Water's chief executive, Bill Alexander, will head new company; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The German utility company RWE A.G. will buy Thames Water P.L.C., of Britain for 6.7 billion [pounds] in cash and assumed debt, about $9.4 billion. The deal values each Thames Water share at $:12.15, or $17.66, a 50 percent premium to their trading average in the last 12 months. The combined company, to be called Thames Water, will be the world's third largest in water and wastewater management, with 34 million customers. Thames Water's chief executive, Bill Alexander, will head the new company.</p>
        <p>Suzanne Kapner</p>
      </block>
